AB  - In order to study a reliable classification model of educational methods, this paper uses improved multi-label transfer learning as the basic algorithm to construct an educational method classification model based on improved multi-label transfer learning. Moreover, this paper restructures the data set into a multi-category data set by coupling other labels to reduce the ratio of unbalanced labels and uses a binary classifier to predict each single label and combines the multi-class classifier and the binary classifier to output the label prediction of the multi-label data. Considering the importance of label information in multi-label data, this paper adds metric migration learning on the basis of transfer learning and proposes a multi-label metric migration learning model MLMTL. With the aid of metric learning, the model effectively retains the inherent geometric information of the feature space and label space. The experimental results demonstrate that the model constructed in this paper is highly effective, with a low distortion rate and high classification accuracy. This indicates that the system is capable of accurately identifying and classifying music education data and provides a reliable and efficient platform for students and teachers to access and manage educational materials. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive licence to Springer-Verlag GmbH Germany, part of Springer Nature.
