AB  - Vocal educators in China face ongoing challenges in effectively transmitting traditional cultural elements in contemporary classrooms. To address this, we explored how the music from the digital game Black Myth: Wukong can be used as a cultural teaching tool in vocal instruction. Using grounded theory and interviews with 30 vocal teachers, we developed a four-part model of ‘digital game–driven cultural communication and vocal teaching innovation’ through three-level coding (Hall, Stuart. 1973. “Encoding/Decoding.” Media Studies 10:128–138). The model illustrates how folklore symbols, immersive interaction, adaptive pedagogy, and cultural identity reinforcement can be sequenced to enhance engagement and learning outcomes. This research provides instructors with a practical pathway for integrating culturally rich, media-based content into vocal music curricula. © 2026 The Author(s). Published by Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
